# Kevin Indig – LinkedIn Research

## Post 1

**Date:** December 2025 *(based on the LinkedIn activity timestamp)*

**Original Link:**  
https://www.linkedin.com/posts/kevinindig_shorter-focused-content-wins-in-chatgpt-activity-7478009571274514439-JjI2

### Summary

Kevin Indig explains that content created for AI-powered search experiences such as ChatGPT should prioritize clarity, focus, and direct answers instead of excessive length. He notes that concise content addressing a single user intent is more likely to be surfaced and cited by AI systems than long pages covering multiple unrelated topics. The post encourages marketers to rethink traditional "longer is better" SEO advice in the context of generative search.

### Main SEO Takeaway

- Write concise, intent-focused content rather than unnecessarily long articles.
- Structure pages so AI systems can easily identify and extract key information.
- Prioritize clarity, relevance, and user intent over word count.
- Optimize content for both traditional search engines and AI-powered search experiences.

